content.description: Start inside the half dome of a rock on the left side of the dry pool from the fallen tree with the two crimps in the middle of the boulder and a bicycle on the left side, reach left hand up to an obvious slopper and right out to a small 2-3 finger bucket. From there move your feet over and slap up and then over the lip to the pocket and top out. The reach out to the bucket and the top are the hardest moves
content.location: The boulder is hidden behind the first boulders that you see, to get to it you will need to walk past the first obvious big boulder on the far side of the creek, keep walking until you find the other fork of the creek and the far cliff side when looking from the road. If you do not see it immediately there should be a large pit where a pool of water once was, if you do not find it you may have to walk up or down the far side of the river. Above the pit there will be a fallen log that hangs over to the middle and inside there is a small half dome boulder, which is Shipwrecked.
